Camp]], led Greek army in [[Greek Civil War]], later [[Field Marshal]] and Prime Minister of Greece.\n|\n* [[Greek Resistance]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | [[Commander-in-Chief]] of the [[Greek Army]] in 1940-41.\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Napoleon Zervas]]\n| [[File:Napoleon Zervas.JPG|100px]]\n| [[Lieutenant Colonel]]\n|\n| Twice minister, died in 1957.\n|\n* [[Greek Resistance]]\n* [[Operation Harling]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Commander of the [[National Republican Greek League]] resistance army.\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Stefanos Sarafis]]\n| \n| [[Major General]]\n|\n| Later MP for the [[United Democratic Left]], died in a car accident in 1957.\n|\n* [[Balkan Campaign (World War II)]]\n* [[Greco-Italian War]]\n* [[Capture of Klisura Pass]]\n* [[Italian Spring Offensive]]\n* [[Battle of Greece]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Founder and chief leader of the [[Greek People's Liberation Army]] (ELAS).\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Aris Velouchiotis]]\n| \n| [[Corporal]] (actual rank)<br>[[Major]] of [[Artillery]] (assumed rank)\n|\n| Committed suicide after the Second World War.\n|\n* [[Greek Resistance]]\n* [[Operation Harling]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Chief military officer of the [[Greek People's Liberation Army]] after April 1943.<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:navy; color:white;\" |'''Navy'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Alexandros Sakellariou]]\n| [[File:On Board the Greek Cruiser Hhms Giorgios Averoff. 23 February 1943, Port-said, Rear Admiral a Sakellariou, Commander in Chief of the Royal Hellenic Navy Flies His Flag in the Cruiser Hhms Giorgios Averoff. A15198.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Vice Admiral]]\n| [[Cross of Valour (Greece)|the Commander's Cross of the Cross of Valour]]\n| MP, Navy and National Defense Minister after the war. Died in 1982.\n|\n* [[Battle of the Mediterranean]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | [[Chief of staff (military)|Chief of staff]] of the [[Royal Hellenic Navy]] 1940-41, [[Minister for National Defence (Greece)|Minister for National Defence]], 1951\u201352\n|}\n\n==== Netherlands ====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000; color:white;\" | Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Henri Winkelman]]\n| [[File:Henri Winkelman.jpg|100px]]\n| [[General]]\n| [[Military William Order]]\n| Died in 1952.\n|\n* [[Battle of the Netherlands]]\n* [[Battle of Maastricht]]\n* [[Battle for The Hague]]\n* [[Battle of Zeeland]]\n* [[Battle of Belgium]]\n* [[Battle of France]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Was [[Commander-in-Chief]] of the Netherlands army during the [[Battle of the Netherlands]].<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Hein ter Poorten]]\n| [[File:Hein ter Poorten.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Lieutenant General]]\n|\n| He spent the rest of the war in various prisoner of war camps, and in 1945 returned to the Netherlands. Died in 1968.\n|\n* [[Netherlands East Indies campaign]]\n* [[Battle of Java (1942)|Battle of Java island]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Commander of the [[American-British-Dutch-Australian Command|ABDA]] land forces in early 1942.\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"background:navy; color:white;\" |'''Navy'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Conrad Helfrich]]\n| [[File:Luitenant-admiraal Helfrich (1946).jpg|100px]]\n| [[Vice Admiral]]\n| [[Order of the Netherlands Lion|Knight Grand Cross of the Order of the Netherlands Lion]]\n| Died in 1962.\n|\n* [[Netherlands East Indi