\"background:#000; color:white;\" | Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Harry Crerar]]\n| [[File:Crerar e010750463-v8.jpg|100px]]\n| [[General]]\n| [[Order of the Companions of Honour]]\n| Became a diplomat, postings in Czechoslovakia, Netherlands and Japan.\n|\n* [[Operation Tractable]]\n* [[Falaise pocket]]\n* [[Operation Astonia]]\n* [[Siege of Dunkirk (1944\u201345)]]\n* [[Battle of the Scheldt]]\n* [[Operation Veritable]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | ''De facto'' [[commander-in-chief]] of the [[Canadian Forces|Canadian military]].<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Guy Simonds]]\n| [[File:Guy Simonds e010778918-v8.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Lieutenant General]]\n| [[Companion of the Order of Canada]]\n| In 1951 he was appointed [[Commander of the Canadian Army|Chief of the General Staff]]\n|\n* [[Operation Atlantic]]\n* [[Battle of Verri\u00e8res Ridge]]\n* [[Operation Spring]]\n* [[Operation Totalize]]\n* [[Operation Tractable]]\n* [[Battle of the Scheldt]]\n* [[Operation Infatuate]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" |Devised the [[Kangaroo (armoured personnel carrier)|Kangaroo]] [[armoured personnel carrier]].<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Andrew McNaughton]]\n| [[File:LGen Andrew McNaughton, 1942 cropped.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Lieutenant General]]\n| [[Order of the Companions of Honour]]\n| First President of the United Nations Security Council\n|\n* [[Minister of National Defence (Canada)|Minister of National Defense]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" |A noteworthy scientist and inventor of a direction finding device for artillery, a precursor to Radar. Fought in [[Vimy Ridge]] during World War I and was a [[lieutenant colonel]]. Commander of the Canadian troops until 1943. Was defeated in the [[Dieppe Raid]]. Opposed the breaking up of the [[Canadian Army]], and insisted it fight as a single unit. Grandfather of [[Lieutenant-General]] [[Andrew Leslie (general)|Andrew Leslie]] of Canada.<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|}\n\n==== South Africa ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000; color:white;\" | Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Jan Smuts]]\n| [[File:JanSmutsFM.png|100px]]\n| [[Field Marshal]]\n| [[L\u00e9gion d'honneur Croix de Commandeur]]\n| Helped drafting of the United Nations Charter, died 11 September 1950\n|\n* [[Imperial War Cabinet]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" |Smuts signed the Paris Peace Treaty, resolving the peace in Europe, thus becoming the only signatory of both the treaty ending the First World War, and that ending the Second.<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|}\n\n==== Luxembourg ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000; color:white;\" | Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[\u00c9mile Speller]]\n| \n| Major-Commandant\n| [[Order of the Oak Crown]]\n| Arrested by Germany in 1940 following the invasion of Luxembourg but later released, died 17 January 1952<ref>{{cite news| title = D\u00e9c\u00e8s du Colonel E. Speller, Aide de Camp de S. A. R. Madame la Grande-Duchesse de Luxembourg:| newspaper = Grand Duch\u00e9 de Luxembourg Minist\u00e9re D'\u00c9tat Bulletin D'Information| location = Luxembourg| volume = 8| issue = 12| page = 30| language = French| publisher = Service information et presse| date = 29 February 