d:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"32\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Ion Antonescu]]\n| [[File:Ion antonescu.png|100px]]\n| [[Marshal of Romania]]\n| [[Order of Michael the Brave]]\n| Executed in 1946.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n* [[Operation M\u00fcnchen]]\n* [[Jassy\u2013Kishinev Offensive|Second Jassy\u2013Kishinev Offensive]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"6\" | Took control of Romania when [[Carol II of Romania|Carol II]] abdicated, and established a fascist dictatorship with the [[Iron Guard]] Party. Acted as Commander-in-Chief of the Romanian Army and [[Conduc\u0103tor]] of Romania, recapturing [[Bessarabia]] and northern [[Bucovina]], then appointed himself marshal. When his forces were decimated at the [[Battle of Stalingrad]], he started negotiating for peace {{Citation needed|date=February 2016}}. His career ended in 1944 when he was arrested by [[Michael of Romania|King Michael]], who signed an armistice with the Allies.<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Petre Dumitrescu]]\n| [[File:Petre Dumitrescu.JPG|100px]]\n| [[General]]\n| [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross|Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]]\n| Died in 1950 after a bout with cancer.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n* [[Operation M\u00fcnchen]]\n* [[Battle of Stalingrad]]\n* [[Dnieper\u2013Carpathian Offensive]]\n* [[First Jassy\u2013Kishinev Offensive]]\n* [[Jassy\u2013Kishinev Offensive|Second Jassy\u2013Kishinev Offensive]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"6\" |Commanded the [[First Army (Romania)|Romanian First Army]] between 1940 and 1941. Commanded the [[Third Army (Romania)|Romanian Third Army]] between 1941 and 1944.\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Constantin Constantinescu-Claps]] \n| \n|[[General officer|General]]\n|[[Order of Michael the Brave]]\n|Died in 1961.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n* [[Battle 