n Front]]\n* [[Battles of Rzhev]]\n* [[Battle of Kursk]]\n* [[Battle of the Dnieper]]\n* [[Battle of Kiev (1943)]]\n* [[Dnieper\u2013Carpathian Offensive]]\n* [[Kamenets-Podolsky pocket]]\n* [[Uman\u2013Boto\u015fani Offensive]]\n* [[First Jassy\u2013Kishinev Offensive]]\n* [[Lvov\u2013Sandomierz Offensive]]\n* [[Battle of the Dukla Pass]]\n* [[Vistula-Oder Offensive]]\n* [[Battle of Berlin]]\n* [[Prague Offensive]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\"|Play a pivotal role in the War, retaking much of Eastern Europe. Helped in the capture of Berlin, the capital of Nazi Germany. Konev was also a competitor of leading star, Marshal Georgy Zhukov.<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Semyon Timoshenko]]\n| [[File:\u041c\u0430\u0440\u0448\u0430\u043b \u0422\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e 1940 01.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Marshal of the Soviet Union]]\n| [[Order of Victory]], Twice [[Hero of the Soviet Union]].\n| Soviet Army commander in Belarus\n|\n* [[Invasion of Poland]]\n* [[Winter War]]\n* [[Battle of Summa]]\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]\n* [[Operation Barbarossa]]\n* [[Battle of Smolensk (1941)]]\n* [[Second Battle of Kharkov]]\n* [[Case Blue]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\"| Defence Commissar till 19 July 1941. Chairman of the Stavka (Soviet High Command). A capable commander in the early stages of World War II. Played a decisive role in the Winter War and the invasion of Poland. After the disaster at Kharkov, Timoshenko was removed by Stalin from front-line command but given overall commanders in different fronts of the USSR.\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| style=\"background:#000001; color:white;\" rowspan=\"6\"|'''Soviet Navy'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ivan Isakov]]\n|[[File:1974 CPA 4359.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Admiral of the Fleet of the Soviet Union]]\n| [[Hero of the Soviet Union]]\n| Commander-in-Chief of the Naval Forces.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]\n* [[Baltic Sea campaigns (1939\u201345)|Baltic Sea campaigns]]\n* [[Battle of the Caucasus]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\"|\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Nikolay Gerasimovich Kuznetsov|Nikolay Kuznetsov]]\n|[[File:Nikolai Kuznetsov 3.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Admiral of the Fleet of the Soviet Union]]\n| [[Hero of the Soviet Union]]\n| People's Commissar of the Navy during The Second World War\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]\n* [[Yalta conference]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\"|\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ivan Yumashev]]\n|[[File:\u0410\u0434\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043b \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u042e\u043c\u0430\u0448\u0435\u0432.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Admiral]]\n| [[Hero of the Soviet Union]]\n| Commander of Soviet Pacific Fleet\n|\n* [[Pacific War]]\n* [[Soviet\u2013Japanese War]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\"|\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| style=\"background:navy; color:white;\" rowspan=\"4\"|'''Soviet Aviation'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Sergei Khudyakov]]\n| [[File:Sergei Khudyakov.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Marshal of Aviation|Marshal of Aviation of the Soviet Union]]\n| [[Order of Lenin]]\n| Chief of Staff of the Air Forces of the Soviet Union, deputy commander of the Red Air Force\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]\n* [[Battles of Rzhev]]\n* [[Battle of Kursk]]\n* [[Yalta conference]]\n* [[Manchurian Strategic Offensive Operation]]\n* [[Soviet\u2013Japanese War]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" |\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Alexander Novikov]]\n| [[File:Alexander Novikov, 1943.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Chief Marshal|Chief Marshal of Aviation of the Soviet Union]]\n| Two times [[Hero of the Soviet Union]]\n| Commander-in-Chief of the Air Forces of the Soviet Union{{clear}}Chief of the High school of civil aviation\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]]\n* [[Axis and Soviet air operations during Operation Barbarossa|Operation Barbarossa]]\n* [[Battle of Kursk]]\n* [[Battle of Stalingrad]]\n* [[Pacific War]]\n|}\n\n==== Republic of China ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000; color:white;\"| Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\"|Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"16\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Chiang Kai-shek]]\n| [[File:Chiang Kai-shek enhanced.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Generalissimo]]\n| [[Order of National Glory]]\n| After [[Second Sino-Japanese War|the war against Japan]], resumed [[Chinese Civil War]] against the communists. Retreated to Taiwan and led the [[Kuomintang]] (KMT) government there until his death.\n|\n* [[Kuomintang|Supreme Leader of the China Front]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"6\"| Was both the head of the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] and the supreme Allied commander in the China Theatre. Led the nation to total war from his temporary capital at Chongqing.\n|- style=\"background:#edf1f1;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Mao Zedong]]\n| [[File:Mao1939.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Chairman of the Communist Party of China|Great Leader of Chinese resistance movements]]\n| [[Honour Sabre of the Awakened Lion]]\n| Defeated the Kuomintang in the [[Chinese Civil War]] and established the [[People's Republic of China]].\n|\n* Organized [[People's war|Chinese guerrilla resistance]] in Japanese-held territories.\n* [[Second Sino-Japanese War]]\n|- style=\"background:#edf1f1;\"\n| colspan=\"6\"| Greatly expanded communist base areas during the war, and eventually usurped control of China from [[Kuomintang]].<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"