 Giorgios Averoff. 23 February 1943, Port-said, Rear Admiral a Sakellariou, Commander in Chief of the Royal Hellenic Navy Flies His Flag in the Cruiser Hhms Giorgios Averoff. A15198.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Vice Admiral]]\n| [[Cross of Valour (Greece)|the Commander's Cross of the Cross of Valour]]\n| MP, Navy and National Defense Minister after the war. Died in 1982.\n|\n* [[Battle of the Mediterranean]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | [[Chief of staff (military)|Chief of staff]] of the [[Royal Hellenic Navy]] 1940-41, [[Minister for National Defence (Greece)|Minister for National Defence]], 1951\u201352\n|}\n\n==== Netherlands ====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000; color:white;\" | Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Henri Winkelman]]\n| [[File:Henri Winkelman.jpg|100px]]\n| [[General]]\n| [[Military William Order]]\n| Died in 1952.\n|\n* [[Battle of the Netherlands]]\n* [[Battle of Maastricht]]\n* [[Battle for The Hague]]\n* [[Battle of Zeeland]]\n* [[Battle of Belgium]]\n* [[Battle of France]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Was [[Commander-in-Chief]] of the Netherlands army during the [[Battle of the Netherlands]].<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Hein ter Poorten]]\n| [[File:Hein ter Poorten.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Lieutenant General]]\n|\n| He spent the rest of the war in various prisoner of war camps, and in 1945 returned to the Netherlands. Died in 1968.\n|\n* [[Netherlands East Indies campaign]]\n* [[Battle of Java (1942)|Battle of Java island]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Commander of the [[American-British-Dutch-Australian Command|ABDA]] land forces in early 1942.\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"background:navy; color:white;\" |'''Navy'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Conrad Helfrich]]\n| [[File:Luitenant-admiraal Helfrich (1946).jpg|100px]]\n| [[Vice Admiral]]\n| [[Order of the Netherlands Lion|Knight Grand Cross of the Order of the Netherlands Lion]]\n| Died in 1962.\n|\n* [[Netherlands East Indies campaign]]\n* [[Battle of the Java Sea]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Commander of the [[American-British-Dutch-Australian Command|ABDA]] Naval forces in 1942.\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Karel Doorman]]\n| [[File:Portrait of Karel Doorman as lieutenant-commander.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Rear admiral]]\n| [[Military William Order|Knight of the Military William Order]]\n| Died in [[Battle of the Java Sea]].\n|\n* [[Netherlands East Indies campaign]]\n* [[Battle of Makassar Strait]]\n* [[Battle of Badung Strait]]\n* [[Battle of the Java Sea]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Commander of the combined American, British, Dutch and Australian ([[ABDA]]) fleet in the [[Dutch East Indies]].<ref name=\"TOCTWW2\" />\n|}\n\n==== Yugoslavia ====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000; color:white;\" | Armed Force\n! colspan=\"2\" |Name\n! Highest Rank\n! Highest Award\n! Fate\n! Theatres / Battles\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#78866b; color:white;\" |'''Army'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Dra\u017ea Mihailovi\u0107]]\n| [[File:Draza Mihailovic,1943.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Army general|General of the Army]]\n| [[Legion of Merit]]\n| Executed by Communists in 1946.\n|\n* [[World War II in Yugoslavia]]\n* [[Chetniks]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" | Led the [[Chetniks]].\n|- style=\"background:#fff;vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Josip Broz Tito]]\n| [[File:Josip Broz Tito Biha\u0107 1942.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Marshal of Yugoslavia|Marshal]]\n| [[Order of the National Hero]]\n| Became [[President of Yugoslavia]]\n|\n*