941. Commanded the [[Third Army (Romania)|Romanian Third Army]] between 1941 and 1944.\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Constantin Constantinescu-Claps]] \n| \n|[[General officer|General]]\n|[[Order of Michael the Brave]]\n|Died in 1961.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n* [[Battle of Stalingrad]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" |Commanded the [[Fourth Army (Romania)|Romanian Fourth Army]] between 1941 and 1943.\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Gheorghe Avramescu]]\n|[[File:Gheorghe Avramescu.jpg|100px]]\n|[[General officer|General]]\n|[[German Cross in Gold]]\n|Died in 1945.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" |Commanded the [[V\u00e2n\u0103tori de munte|Romanian Mountain Corps]] between 1941 and 1943. Commanded the [[Fourth Army (Romania)|Romanian Fourth Army]] between 1944 and 1945.\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Ioan Mihail Racovi\u021b\u0103]]\n|[[File:MihailRacovita.jpg|frameless|138x138px]]\n|[[General officer|General]]\n|[[Order of Michael the Brave]]\n|Died in 1954.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" |Commanded the Romanian Cavalry Corps  between 1941 and 1943. Commanded the Romanian Mechanized Troops between 1943 and 1944.\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Vasile Atanasiu]]\n|[[File:Vasile Atanasiu.png|frameless|138x138px]]\n|[[General officer|General]]\n|[[Order of the White Lion]]\n|Died in 1964.\n|\n* [[Eastern Front (World War II)]]\n* [[Prague Offensive]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" |Commanded the 3rd Army Corps in the liberation of [[Bessarabia]], the battle for the [[beachhead]] of [[Albi\u0163a, Vaslui|Albi\u0163a]] on the [[Prut River]], the advance to the [[Dniester]] at [[Tiraspol]] between 1941 and 1943. Commanded the [[First Army (Romania)|Romanian First Army]] in 1945, in the battles on the Czechoslovakian front in the [[Javorina]], between the rivers [[Hron]] and [[Morava (river)|Morava]] and thereafter in [[Bohemia]].\n|